  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 364c2b772391e46dba637935c558b9b2, type: 3}
  m_Name: Myth_59
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::MythSO
  pageNumber: 59
  mythName: Myth 59
  omens:
  - '1. A field littered with martial detritus.

    Broken helms, shields, and bodies.
    The

    mud grabs at those passing over, groans

    on the wind. A lean horse
    is trying to pull

    its dead rider from the ground to no avail.'
  - '2. A lone legionnaire deserter. Can only

    grunt in cowardice, scouring the
    land for

    a place to hide. A pack of 5 legionnaires

    are tracking them,
    minutes away.'
  - '3. A local militia are camped, recovering

    from a clash with the Legion.
    Few are

    dead, but the wounded cry in agony. The

    lacerations of the
    Legion''s barbed blades

    are as fresh as when they were cut.'
  - '4. A Legion Warband on the horizon, firing

    their arrows at the farthest
    possible

    range. Break into retreat if approached.'
  - '5. A new legionnaire pulling themselves

    from the earth. Pained, clutching
    rusted

    arms. Seeks the comfort of the Legion.'
  - '6. Three Legion Warbands invade the

    nearest Holding. If defeated they return

    in
    greater ranks. The war only ends if

    they are driven into fire or water.'
  verse: 
  castEntries:
  - name: Legionnaires, Born of Mud and Blood
    statBlock: 'VIG 15, CLA 5, SPI 5, 3 GD

      A3 (rusted mail, helm, shield)'
    notes: 'Barbed blade (d8), shield (d4), bow (d6 long),

      all deal wounds
      that resist natural healing.

      Fear of death. No purpose beyond war.'
  - name: Graveyard Horse, Greyveil
    statBlock: 'VIG 10, CLA 10, SPI 5, 2 GD

      Instinctive reverence for the
      dead, always'
    notes: knows where they should be taken to.
  - name: Local Militia, Untrained Serfs
    statBlock: 'VIG 10, CLA 10, SPI 10, 2 GD

      Polearms (d10 long), patchwork
      uniforms'
    notes: 'Pitly ranks, fought and fell, returning stronger still

      Their scars
      nae fade, their fear but grow, their war their only will

      SCARS FROM
      THE LAST DEATH

      Location Description

      1 Face Pierced

      2 Arm
      Burned

      3 Leg Crushed

      4 Torso Whipped

      5 Back Mangled

      6
      Head Sliced

      Legion

      Dwelling: Cooling well ~ Sanctum: Sparkling
      crags ~ Monument: Cleaved mountain

      Hazard: Spiked roots ~ Curse: Groaning
      earth ~ Ruin: Ash-drowned town

      The'
